data.meta_description: French Nobility, Heir Presumptive of Spain. Charles de France, son of Louis, Dauphin of France, and his wife Duchess Maria Anna Victoria of Bavaria, was born at the Palace of Versailles. He was given the title of Duke of Berry at his birth.
